                <h4 class="heading"><strong>WHAT IS A MENTORSHIP?</strong></h4>
                <p id="pM1">

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            A Mentorship is a relationship in which a more experienced or more knowledgeable person helps to guide a less experienced or less
                            knowledgeable person.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            It is a learning and development partnership between someone with vast experience and someone who wants to learn.
                            Interaction with an expert may also be necessary to gain proficiency with/in cultural tools.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Mentorship experience and relationship structure affect the amount of psychosocial support, career guidance, role modeling, and
                            communication that occurs in the mentoring relationships in which the protégés and mentors engaged.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <hr />
                <h4 class="heading"><strong>WHY DO YOU NEED MENTORSHIP?</strong></h4>
                <p id="pM1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            We need to have valuable Mentorship in our lives. We want to have a viable model of someone as we progress along our professional path.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <hr />
                <h4 class="heading"><strong>WHEN YOU HAVE A MENTORSHIP?</strong></h4>
                <p id="pM1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            During the connection and building phases of a Mentorship, the Mentoree and Mentor Benefit from the value of the interaction.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <hr />
                <h4 class="heading"><strong>WHAT ARE CHARACTERISTICS OF A GOOD MENTOR?</strong></h4>
                <p id="pM1">
                    <h5>When you become a Mentoree, the Mentor should have:</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">QUESTIONS:</h6>
                            Have questions to ask and have goals set for your professional career.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">RESOURCES:</h6>
                            Education is key, be open to receiving Instructions, Books, Courses, and then implement the action.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">INTERACTION:</h6>
                            Plan and schedule Coffee/Tea,Lunch with Mentors in a positive environment.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">NETWORK:</h6>
                            Be present, attend events, meet people, and make connections
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <hr />
                <h4 class="heading"><strong>WHAT ARE CHARACTERISTICS OF A GOOD MENTOREE?</strong></h4>
                <p id="pM1">
                    <h5>When you become a Mentor, the Mentoree should have:</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">QUESTIONS:</h6>
                            Provide answers and guidance to the questions Mentoree have regarding their goals set for a professional career.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">RESOURCES:</h6>
                            Education is key, provide advisement in Instructions, Books, Courses, and suggested tools you have experience with.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">INTERACTION:</h6>
                            Plan and schedule Coffee/Tea,Lunch with Mentoree in a positive environment.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <h6 style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline">NETWORK:</h6>
                            Be present, attend events, meet people, and make connections
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
